Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and halve @carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise. Dice @roma tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with half the @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and sear until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side (it'll finish cooking later). TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion, carrot, half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), remaining Tunisian Spice, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Israeli couscous{3/4%cup}, @dried apricots{1%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 2 cups @water{2%cups}, and ½ tsp salt into pan with veggies. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium; place chicken in the center of pan. Cook, covered, until chicken is cooked through, couscous is tender, and liquid is mostly absorbed, ~{6-8%minutes} TIP: For thinner chicken cutlets, check doneness after 5 minutes; remove if cooked through. Check on couscous periodically; if liquid evaporates before it's done, add splashes of water as needed. Or, if you end up with any excess liquid, remove chicken, then increase heat to medium high and continue cooking until excess liquid evaporates.

Meanwhile, zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @pistachios{1.5%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, remaining @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of lemon zest. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Remove chicken from pan; set aside to rest.

Stir tomato, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice into pan with couscous. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous between plates; top with chicken. Drizzle sauce over chicken. Garnish with pistachios and as much lemon zest as you like. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> For 4 servings, double the Tunisian spice blend, couscous, chicken, chicken stock concentrate, dried apricots, sour cream, cooking oil, and butter amounts. Also use 4 cups water and 1 tsp salt when cooking the couscous.